        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 7:23PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 723 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Carsonville to Peck to near Lum. Movement was
southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Croswell, Yale, Port Sanilac, Applegate, and Melvin around 730 PM
EDT.
Lexington around 735 PM EDT.
Emmett around 750 PM EDT.
Lakeport around 755 PM EDT.
Port Huron around 810 PM EDT.
Marysville around 820 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include North Street,
Goodland Township, Birch Beach, Lynn Township, Amador, Goodells,
Brockway, Smiths Creek, Valley Center, and Wadhams.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
